The home health agency and the hospice protocol shall include but not be limited to the following:
Safe and secure storage of drugs;
Access to drugs limited to authorized employees;
Records of drugs checked out to authorized employees and records of drugs, amounts, and to whom and by whom administered;
Prompt notification of the pharmacy when a drug is used, including the prescriber, patient, drug, dosage form, directions for use and other pertinent information;
Billing information;
Procedures for handling drugs beyond their expiration date; and
Inventory control.

The following legend drugs shall be allowed under these agreements:
Sterile water for injection or irrigation;
Sterile saline solution for injection or irrigation;
Heparin flush solution;
Diphenhydramine injectable;
Epinephrine injectable;
Glucagon;
Influenza vaccine; and
Pneumonia vaccine.
